James S. Crook

For further information on findfiles: https://yosj.com.au/staff/c_programs/findfiles/findfiles.html

For Linux and Cygwin
    gcc -o findfiles findfiles.c

    gcc -O2 -Wall -Wpedantic -Wextra -Wshadow -Wpointer-arith -Wcast-qual -o findfiles findfiles.c
	Fedora Linux:	clean compiles
	OpenSuse Linux: warns about USAGEMESSAGE being > 509 character long

    -Wpedantic -> -pedantic and link with -lrt:
    gcc -O2 -Wall  -pedantic -Wextra -Wshadow -Wpointer-arith -Wcast-qual -o findfiles findfiles.c -lrt
	SLES:		warns about USAGEMESSAGE being > 509 character long

For AIX:
    gcc -maix64 -o findfiles findfiles.c
